SUPPORT COMMUNICATION - SECURITY BULLETIN

Document ID: c04924053
Version: 1

HPSBGN03530 rev.1 - HPE UCMDB Browser, Remote Disclosure of Sensitive
Information, Local Unauthorized Access

NOTICE: The information in this Security Bulletin should be acted upon as
soon as possible.

Release Date: 2016-01-06
Last Updated: 2016-01-06

Potential Security Impact: Remote Disclosure of Information, Local
Unauthorized Access

Source: Hewlett Packard Enterprise, Product Security Response Team

VULNERABILITY SUMMARY
A potential security vulnerability has been identified in HPE UCMDB Browser.
The vulnerability could be exploited to allow remote disclosure of sensitive
information and result in local unauthorized access.

Note: This vulnerability only impacts customers using UCMDB browser.

References:

CVE-2015-6862
PSRT102975

SUPPORTED SOFTWARE VERSIONS*: ONLY impacted versions are listed.
HPE UCMDB Browser - All versions prior to v4.02.

BACKGROUND

CVSS 2.0 Base Metrics
===========================================================
  Reference              Base Vector             Base Score
CVE-2015-6862    (AV:L/AC:L/Au:N/C:C/I:C/A:C)       7.2
===========================================================
             Information on CVSS is documented
            in HP Customer Notice: HPSN-2008-002

RESOLUTION

HPE has made the following mitigation information available to resolve the
vulnerability in HPE UCMDB Browser:

For all versions prior to v4.02, upgrade to v4.02 or newer.

Download Link: https://hpln.hpe.com//node/9462/contentfiles?dir=25648

